The President expresses deep concern over the security situation in Cote d'Ivoire and supports the United Nations peacekeepers and French forces in their efforts to protect civilians. He blames former President Laurent Gbagbo for the violence, stating that it could have been avoided if Gbagbo had respected the results of the previous year's presidential election. The President calls for Gbagbo to step down immediately and for his supporters to lay down their arms to prevent further bloodshed. He emphasizes the suffering of the people of Cote d'Ivoire and expresses concern over reports of massacres in the western region. The President calls on all parties to show restraint and respect the rights of the people, and he welcomes President Alassane Ouattara's commitment to holding those responsible for attacks against civilians accountable. The United States will continue to support a future where Gbagbo steps down and President Ouattara and the government can move beyond the crisis and serve the people of Cote d'Ivoire.